id: pm-b9ov
title: "GH-454: schema add-field accepts reserved built-in names silently; collision error names no partner"
description: "Dogfood GH-454: registering a reserved built-in name (customer_impact) via add-field succeeds silently, then extension collisions produce a partner-less misleading error; in the dogfood the combination broke all Task creates. CLI/config-side twin of pm-ghf1 (SDK lint/preflight side). Duplicate check: pm-ghf1 covers only the SDK surface; no other overlap."
