close_reason: "Reserved schema/extension collisions now fail at registration/use with both claimants, rename guidance, and the full denylist; regression and packed-package proof passed."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/454\n\n## Problem\n(1) `pm schema add-field` accepts reserved built-in field names (e.g. customer_impact — an existing create flag) with no warning; (2) when an extension later registers the same name, the runtime error \"collides with reserved item metadata\" names neither the reserved-ness nor the collision partner; in the GH-454 dogfood the config-field + extension-field combination broke ALL pm create Task calls.\n\n## Proposed fix\nadd-field validates against the reserved/built-in name list at registration time (error, or --force with warning); collision errors name both claimants (config field vs extension field vs reserved metadata) with a rename hint. Share the same RESERVED_ITEM_FIELD_NAMES source pm-ghf1 exports to the SDK — this is the CLI/config-side twin of that SDK-side item.\n\n## Definition of done\nadd-field on a reserved name fails fast with the reserved list; collision error names both parties; shared constant with runtime + SDK (drift spec); repro from GH-454 covered by spec."
